  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Tissue hypoxia is one of the most important factors leading to the development of multiorgan
      failure. Patients presenting for emergent major abdominal surgery might suffer from organ
      hypoperfusion. Thus, early detection of the imbalance between oxygen supply and demand may
      improve the outcome. The investigators believe that hypoperfusion of the abdominal organs
      will cause a decrease of the saturation in the hepatic vein and in the IVC.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
